HEADWORD: Endolymphatic
<hw>En"do*lym*phat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Endo-</ets> + <ets>lymphatic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Pertaining to, or containing, endolymph; <as>as, the
<ex>endolymphatic</ex> duct</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Within a
lymphatic vessel; endolymphangial.</def>⟦br⟧
